    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-03T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-10-03T04:00:00-05:00" n="288"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d288">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_CFM1">CFM</gloss> Files</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">United States Delegation Journal</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-chapter-heading" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1946-10-03T10:00:00+01:00">October 3, 1946, 10 a.m.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> (PC) (Journal) 60</p>
                <p>The text of the report on the military clauses of the draft treaty with Rumania
                    was provisionally adopted.<note n="74" xml:id="d288fn1">For text of the report,
                        C.P. (Plen) Doc. 18, October 5, see <ref target="frus1946v04#pg_476">vol.
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, p. 476</ref>.</note> The footnote to
                    the conclusion in the original text was deleted and an insertion made after
                    Article 14 in the report. The insertion was made on a proposal by General
                        <persName>Balmer</persName> and stated that the resolution, originally
                    proposed by the U.S. Delegation, which stated that the articles on limitations
                    in the Balkan and Finnish treaties should be identical, was accepted
                        unanimously.<note n="75" xml:id="d288fn2">Debate centered around the Soviet
                        Delegate’s contention that article 14 of the Rumanian treaty was based on
                        article 44 of the Italian treaty. General <persName>Balmer</persName> stated
                        that it was based on article 12 of the Bulgarian treaty. See the United
                        States Delegation Journal accounts of the 14th Meeting, September 11, and
                        the 28th Meeting, September 28, <ref target="#pg_420">pp. 420</ref> and <ref
                            target="#pg_584">584</ref>, respectively.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
